column5: Several OFC'ers were going into this derby today. Anyone know how big the $1500 winning fish was? How did everybody do?
Sat And Sunday it's over sunday at 4pm I beleive Richard
As of yesterday best pike was 25". Today i didn't have time to get out so don't know whos the leader.
I heard 37" was the leader with a couple 34" 's behind it.  This was of 2PM yesterday afternoon
it's good to hear that there are a few big ones in the lake. 37" that should be the winning pike.
Hey Jose, I don't think we'd have had 37 inches total...lol
I had a buddy's son go this year,all I know is his girlfriend kicked there butts , we're meeting shortly to head out how did every body here do Richard
So true Curt but there is next year. We got into some fish but all small but still better then last year with a fat skunk behinde us next year should be better.
